Maclay Murray & Spens LLP is one of Scotland's largest commercial law firms, with offices in Edinburgh, London and Aberdeen and headquartered in Glasgow.

The firm was founded in 1871 in Glasgow by David Maclay, David Murray and John Spens as the first law firm in Scotland with a specifically commercial practice. Its practice areas now encompass: Banking &amp; Finance; Capital Projects; Commercial Dispute Resolution; Construction & Engineering; Corporate; Employment, Pensions & Benefits; EU, Competition & Regulatory; Housing & Care;  & Technology; Planning & Environmental; Private Client; Property; and Tax.

